The STOP-Trial is a prospective multicenter nonrandomized open study on grade I hypertension, performed by General Practitioners.

 The main purpose of the study is to determine the factors associated with the rate of patients remaining normotensive one year after stopping their antihypertensive monotherapy or low dose dual therapy: - white coat hypertension - primary diagnosis by home blood pressure measurements (HBPM) /ambulatory blood pressure measurements (ABPM) /clinical measure - initial blood pressure level - compliance - therapeutic class versus others - age - gender - weight variation - modification of lifestyle - concomitant treatments and associated substances The primary endpoint will be the rate of normotensive patients at one year (i.

